probe+ui: per-host "Talking to" view (active conversations + reverse DNS)

The agent detail page can now show what each host is actually talking
to, not just what ports it's exposing.

Probe (Snapshot v2):
- Replace collectListeners with collectSockets: single pass over
  net.Connections that produces both Listeners and a new
  Conversations slice.
- Conversation aggregation by (proto, direction, remote_ip,
  remote_port, process). Direction inferred from listener overlap
  (inbound = local port matches one of our listeners; outbound
  otherwise). TIME_WAIT and SYN_SENT dropped as noise. Loopback
  peers excluded. Capped at 200 rows.
- New dnscache.go: process-local TTL'd reverse-DNS resolver
  (1h positive / 5m negative) with bounded parallel workers
  (8 in-flight, 500ms per lookup, 4s total budget).
- Schema bump 1 -> 2.

API:
- No schema migration needed: rides in last_metrics JSONB.
- OpenAPI doc-only update describing the v2 conversations array.

UI:
- AgentDetail: new "Talking to" section (counts header,
  outbound/inbound/all toggle, free-text filter across host/IP/port/
  process, scrollable table with direction pill, peer host+IP, port,
  proto, process+pid, state, conn count).
- types.ts: SnapshotConversation + optional conversations on Snapshot.

Version 2026.4.25.6.
